The paper focuses on object proposal generation and visual tracking, which are both computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves integrating information and ranking strategies, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of context information and the generation of object proposals, which are related to deep learning and large-scale learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to video-related tasks, which can be related to multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a tracker that uses the generated object proposals, which can be related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category.
